"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses np.insert on a numpy array. The np.insert function returns a new array and does not modify the array in place. Therefore, the assignment arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3) is incorrect because it changes the shape of the sub-array, which will lead to a ValueError since the shape of arr[i] will no longer match the original shape of arr.\",\n  \"patch\": \"6c6\\n<    arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n>    arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)[:4]\"\n}"